And personally I’ve learned this the hard way, there is a specific pain with being self aware of why you act a certain way

But the best way to cope with it is to admit you did wrong and try to reconcile, even if it’s something relatively small like a miscommunication
I know its hard bc trauma inherently makes it feel like the world is against you, but i promise it’s better for you and everyone else in the long run to say sorry than to fight constantly
Part of healing from trauma is recognizing when you are in the wrong and being able to honestly apologize for your actions

Im gonna mute this but if you are going to commission someone pls don’t feel bad for asking for an update now and then, you at least deserve that much courtesy

And look im a very slow artist so i do my best to tell my commissioners “hey i just want to let you know this one thing is gonna set me back” and most ppl I’ve worked with have been understanding, you have to communicate with ppl if you wanna do this kinda work

ofc there is a limit and there are ppl that are *actually* entitled, but at the end of the day they payed for your service and they want to trust that they will get what they paid for that’s not a bad thing
commissioners are not rude for asking for something as small as an update, if anything we should be encouraging our clients to ask for updates or let us know if they are dissatisfied
